1) Demands dueâ€‘process protections (notice + hearing) and cites your circuitâ€™s test;
2) Shows your filing history with outcomes and colorable claims (table/exhibit index);
3) Attacks any improper findings as conclusory and not supported by the record;
4) Proposes concrete, **narrow** alternatives (scope, parties, timeâ€‘limit, leaveâ€‘ofâ€‘court criteria).

