ğŸ“– Lesson Content
â€¢ Preserve Immediately â±ï¸ â€” Calendar Rule 59(e)/52(b) (28 days), Rule 54(b) reconsideration for interlocutory orders, and objections under Rule 72. If you will appeal, compute the FRAP 4 deadline and note any tolling motions (59/50/52/60 filed â‰¤28 days).
â€¢ Clarify the Order ğŸ§­ â€” Move to clarify/amend to identify: the grounds relied on, the exhibits reviewed, and the scope ('without prejudice' vs. 'with prejudice'). Ask for explicit findings or a short statement of reasons sufficient for review.
â€¢ Fix the Record ğŸ“š â€” File a Motion to Correct/Supplement the record (FRCP 60(a) / FRAP 10(e)) if exhibits, dates, or docket entries are missing/misdescribed. Attach proof of tender/receipt and a proposed correction.
â€¢ Stack Doctrines ğŸ§  â€” Frame alternative bases: e.g., dueâ€‘process (notice/opportunity), First Amendment retaliation, accessâ€‘toâ€‘courts, badâ€‘faith Younger exception, and equitable factors (Winter/Nken) if injunctive relief is implicated. Preserve each with pinpoint citations.
â€¢ Protect Status Quo ğŸ›‘ â€” Consider stay pending appeal (Rule 62 / FRAP 8) or an administrative stay; propose security and a narrow order.
â€¢ Map the Posture ğŸ—ºï¸ â€” Build a oneâ€‘page Postâ€‘Denial Map: issue list â†’ standard of review â†’ record cite â†’ remedy requested on appeal. Decide which issues are jurisdictional, purely legal (de novo), or discretionary (abuse of discretion).
â€¢ Set the Appeal â–¶ï¸ â€” File a clean Notice of Appeal; designate the record; draft a targeted Appendix/Excerpts index; order transcripts or prepare 10(c) statements if needed.
ğŸ“ Assignment
